### Configuration
@baseUrl = http://localhost:3000/api
@projectId = YOUR_PROJECT_ID_AFTER_CREATE
@findingId = YOUR_FINDING_ID_AFTER_ADD

### 1. Create a New Project
# This initializes ProjectVersion v1 and copies the Active Template
POST {{baseUrl}}/projects
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "External Pentest - April 2026",
  "companyId": "REPLACE_WITH_COMPANY_ID_FROM_SEED",
  "serviceId": "REPLACE_WITH_SERVICE_ID_FROM_SEED",
  "createdBy": "REPLACE_WITH_USER_ID_FROM_SEED"
}

### 2. Get Project Details
# Retrieves project metadata and its current version data
GET {{baseUrl}}/projects/{{projectId}}


### 3. Add a New Finding
# Auto-assigns displayId (e.g., WEB-01) and order
POST {{baseUrl}}/projects/{{projectId}}/findings
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "SQL Injection in Login Form",
  "severity": "CRITICAL",
  "description": "An attacker can bypass authentication by injecting SQL commands.",
  "remediation": "Use parameterized queries or prepared statements.",
  "evidence": ["https://s3.amazonaws.com/vapt/evidence1.png"]
}


### 4. Add another Finding (to test reordering)
POST {{baseUrl}}/projects/{{projectId}}/findings
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "title": "Cross-Site Scripting (XSS)",
  "severity": "HIGH",
  "description": "Script injection possible via the search bar.",
  "remediation": "Implement proper output encoding.",
  "evidence": []
}


### 5. Reorder Findings
# Updates the 'order' field for a list of findings
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/projects/{{projectId}}/findings/reorder
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "orderedIds": [
    "SECOND_FINDING_ID",
    "FIRST_FINDING_ID"
  ]
}